+## Retry Shape For Checkbox-54
+
+When checkbox-54 is retried, the supervisor should constrain the daemon to one of these narrow cycles.
+
+Cycle A: syntax-first contract skeleton
+
+- Edit only `ppd/contracts/source_freshness.py` and one focused import/compile test if needed.
+- Define small dataclasses or plain functions only after validating that the file compiles.
+- Keep type annotations conventional Python, for example `recrawl_cadence_days: int | None`, never annotation fragments inside an `if` condition.
+- Avoid validators that depend on fixture shape beyond simple dictionary keys.
+- Require `python3 -m py_compile ppd/contracts/source_freshness.py` before full PP&D validation.
+
+Cycle B: tiny freshness fixture
+
+- Edit only `ppd/tests/fixtures/source_freshness/source_freshness_fixture.json` or a similarly named source-freshness fixture path plus the focused test that loads it.
+- Include exactly one stale page, one changed-hash page, one removed page, and one recrawl-priority example.
+- Use deterministic timestamps and hashes.
+- Do not include response bodies, downloaded document paths, traces, screenshots, credentials, private DevHub paths, live crawl output, or session files.
+
+Cycle C: focused classifier assertions
+
+- Edit only the source-freshness contract and focused test.
+- Validate classification names and priority ordering only.
+- Do not add change-report rendering, live recrawl scheduling, archive processor integration, or broader source-index rewrites in the same cycle.
+
+## General Syntax-Failure Guardrails
+
+For any retry after a Python `SyntaxError` or `py_compile` failure:
+
+- Prefer one Python file plus one test file at most.
+- Ask the worker for the smallest syntactically valid repair that can pass `py_compile` before adding fixture breadth.
+- Avoid long generated helper functions.
+- Avoid nested f-strings, inline regex construction, complex comprehensions, and multiline string literals in generated code.
+- Keep rejection reasons and classification names as module-level string constants.
+- Keep dataclass field annotations on field lines, not inside conditionals or expressions.
+- Use simple explicit conditionals over clever one-liners.
+- Run py_compile before full PP&D validation and treat any compile failure as a syntax-preflight failure, not as a normal unit-test failure.
+
+For any retry after TypeScript `TS1005`, `TS1109`, or `TS1128`:
+
+- Prefer one TypeScript file at most.
+- Avoid broad type contract rewrites.
+- Keep interfaces and object literals small.
+- Run the TypeScript command before broader tests.
 
