+## Acceptance Criteria For Syntax-Failure Recovery
+
+A task with repeated syntax failures may be retried only when all are true:
+
+- The next proposal is constrained to the smallest file set needed for syntax-valid repair.
+- Every changed Python file compiles with `py_compile` before broad tests.
+- Every changed TypeScript file is checked by the PP&D TypeScript command before dependent tests.
+- The proposal does not broaden scope into unrelated contracts, live crawling, DevHub automation, or report rendering.
+- The proposal keeps fixtures deterministic, redacted, committed under `ppd/tests/fixtures/`, and free of private or live artifacts.
+
+## Acceptance Criteria For Unblocking Checkbox-54
+
+Checkbox-54 may be considered unblocked only when all are true:
+
+- `ppd/contracts/source_freshness.py` compiles with py_compile.
+- The focused source-freshness tests pass without live network access.
+- Fixture examples cover stale guidance, changed content hashes, removed pages, and recrawl priority.
+- No committed fixture contains raw response bodies, credentials, trace paths, screenshot paths, downloaded document paths, private DevHub paths, or live crawl artifacts.
+- The change does not implement live recrawl behavior or authenticated DevHub automation.
+
